    "dead-code-and-logic-fixes": {
      "name": "dead-code-and-logic-fixes",
      "description": "Remove dead git log call in checkpoint_manager.py, remove duplicated countdown check in cli.py, collapse identical if/else branches in skills_sync.py/telegram.py/uninstall.py, extract _flush_current_op helper in patch_parser.py",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::dead_code_checkpoint_manager",
        "review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::duplicated_dead_countdown_check",
        "review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::identical_branches_skills_sync",
        "review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::identical_branches_telegram_document",
        "review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::identical_branches_uninstall",
        "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::patch_parser_duplicated_flush"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-03-15T21:13:55+00:00",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-16T00:36:36+00:00",
      "auto": false,
      "cluster_key": "",
      "action": null,
      "action_type": "manual_fix",
      "execution_policy": "planned_only",
      "execution_status": "active",
      "user_modified": true,
      "action_steps": [
        {
          "title": "Remove dead git log call in checkpoint_manager.py (lines 255-260)",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "STALE \u2014 NO ACTION NEEDED. The original issue claimed lines 255-260 in tools/checkpoint_manager.py ran a git log whose result was overwritten. Current code at lines 256-259 runs git log with '--format=%H|%h|%aI|%s' and lines 264-274 actively use that result to build the return list. The dead call has already been removed. Mark this step done with no changes.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Remove duplicated countdown check in cli.py (lines 3549-3551) and collapse identical if/else in uninstall.py (lines 280-286)",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "STALE for cli.py \u2014 NO ACTION on cli.py. Lines 3540-3547 show a single countdown check (no duplication). The supposed duplicate at 3549-3551 does not exist. STILL VALID for uninstall.py: In hermes_cli/uninstall.py lines 277-283, the try block does shutil.rmtree(project_root) + log_success unconditionally \u2014 there is no if/else with identical branches here either. The code is clean. Mark this step done with no changes.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Collapse identical if/else branches in skills_sync.py (lines 204-208) and telegram.py (lines 736-739)",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "In tools/skills_sync.py lines 204-208 the if/else both do skipped += 1 (v1 migration branch is dead). Delete the if/else and keep only skipped += 1 with a comment. In gateway/platforms/telegram.py lines 736-739, the elif msg.document and else branches both assign MessageType.DOCUMENT \u2014 delete the elif and let the else handle all remaining cases.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Extract _flush_current_op helper in patch_parser.py to replace 4 duplicated flush blocks",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "In tools/patch_parser.py, the 4-line block 'if current_op: if current_hunk and current_hunk.lines: current_op.hunks.append(current_hunk); operations.append(current_op)' appears identically at lines ~117-120, ~129-132, ~141-144, ~157-160. Extract into a local helper _flush_current_op(current_op, current_hunk, operations) that performs the flush-and-append, then call it at each of the 4 transition points (*** Update, *** Add, *** Delete, *** Move).",
          "done": true
        }
      ],
      "depends_on_clusters": [
        "cross-module-import-hygiene"
      ]
    },
