      "execution_policy": "planned_only",
      "execution_status": "active",
      "user_modified": true,
      "action_steps": [
        {
          "title": "Review the verbose docstrings in toolsets.py",
          "detail": "In toolsets.py: replace verbose Args/Returns docstrings on small functions with single-line docstrings. Confirmed present: get_toolset() at line 300 has 10-line docstring with Args/Returns for a 1-line function. Replace with: 'Return toolset definition by name, or None.' Same for resolve_toolset(), get_all_toolsets(), get_toolset_names(), get_toolset_info() and other short functions. Count: approximately 8-10 functions need shortened docstrings.",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Delete inline statements restating code logic",
          "detail": "In toolsets.py at line 311: remove '# Return toolset definition' comment before 'return TOOLSETS.get(name)' \u2014 comment restates code. Scan for other restating inline comments: look for '# Return ...', '# Get ...', '# Check ...' followed by code that already makes the action obvious. Verified present at line 311.",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Modify toolset_distributions.py to strip stale probability comments",
          "detail": "In toolset_distributions.py: remove inline probability comments that contradict the numeric values. Confirmed stale: line 48 'image_gen: 90  # 80% chance' (comment says 80, value is 90), line 49 'vision: 90  # 60% chance' (says 60, is 90), line 50 'web: 55  # 40% chance' (says 40, is 55), line 52 'moa: 10  # 20% chance' (says 20, is 10). Remove all these inline percentage comments \u2014 the numeric values are self-documenting. Do not remove the description strings in the outer dict.",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "done": true
        }
      ],
      "depends_on_clusters": [
        "type-safety-annotations"
      ]
    },
    "type-safety-annotations": {
      "name": "type-safety-annotations",
      "description": "Add Optional[] annotations where None is returned, fix SendResult return type in delivery.py, add Literal types for api_mode/reset_mode discriminators in run_agent.py and gateway/config.py",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::type_safety::optional_without_annotation",
        "review::.::holistic::type_safety::message_event_source_not_optional",
        "review::.::holistic::type_safety::adapters_dict_any_any",
        "review::.::holistic::type_safety::untyped_discriminator_api_mode",
        "review::.::holistic::type_safety::untyped_discriminator_reset_mode",
        "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::toolset_info_returns_none"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-03-15T21:13:59+00:00",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-15T23:50:13+00:00",
      "auto": false,
      "cluster_key": "",
      "action": null,
      "action_type": "manual_fix",
      "execution_policy": "planned_only",
      "execution_status": "active",
      "user_modified": true,
      "action_steps": [
        {
          "title": "Add Optional[] annotations in run_agent.py and toolsets.py where None is accepted/returned",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "In run_agent.py: AIAgent.__init__ params (lines 215-257) use bare 'str = None', 'int = None' etc. without Optional[]. Change: base_url: str = None \u2192 base_url: Optional[str] = None; api_key: Optional[str] = None; provider: Optional[str] = None; api_mode: Optional[str] = None; session_id: Optional[str] = None; platform: Optional[str] = None; honcho_session_key: Optional[str] = None. In toolsets.py: get_toolset_info() at line 446 annotated as -> Dict[str, Any] but returns None at line 458 \u2014 change to -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]. Optional import is already present in both files.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Fix return type annotation in delivery.py to SendResult and add Optional to source field in MessageEvent",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "In gateway/platforms/base.py: MessageEvent.source at line 283 is typed as 'source: SessionSource = None' \u2014 annotation should be 'source: Optional[SessionSource] = None' since it defaults to None. Check delivery.py for SendResult return type annotation. In gateway/delivery.py: find functions returning SendResult-like values and verify annotation accuracy.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Add Literal types for api_mode and reset_mode discriminators, type adapters dict in channel_directory.py",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "In run_agent.py: add 'ApiMode = Literal[\"chat_completions\", \"codex_responses\", \"anthropic_messages\"]' near the top-level typing imports, then change 'api_mode: str = None' in AIAgent.__init__ (line 218) to 'api_mode: Optional[ApiMode] = None'. In gateway/config.py line 64, ResetMode is already defined as Literal; verify SessionResetPolicy.mode (line 77) is typed as ResetMode. In gateway/channel_directory.py line 44, change 'Dict[Any, Any]' to 'Dict[Platform, BasePlatformAdapter]'.",
          "done": true
        }
      ],
      "depends_on_clusters": [
        "aiagent-constructor-config"
      ]
    },
