        {
          "title": "Locate image/audio cache getters",
          "detail": "In gateway/platforms/base.py: three get_*_cache_dir functions exist at lines 49 (get_image_cache_dir), 131 (get_audio_cache_dir), 199 (get_document_cache_dir). All three create the directory as a side effect (mkdir call on lines 51, 133, 201) \u2014 misleading names. They are referenced at 6 call sites within base.py itself. This step: identify all callers via grep, confirm only base.py internal usage, and prepare rename plan.",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [
            "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::cache_getters_mutate_filesystem"
          ],
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Extract unified MediaCache class",
          "detail": "In gateway/platforms/base.py: extract a MediaCache class from the triplicated pattern. The three sets (image: lines 45-118, audio: 128-177, document: 187-255) share identical structure. Add at line ~45:\n\nclass MediaCache:\n    def __init__(self, media_type: str, cache_subdir: str):\n        self.media_type = media_type\n        self._cache_dir = Path.home() / '.hermes' / 'cache' / cache_subdir\n\n    def ensure_dir(self) -> Path:\n        self._cache_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n        return self._cache_dir\n\n    def cache_from_bytes(self, data: bytes, ext: str) -> Path:\n        self.ensure_dir()\n        filename = f'{uuid.uuid4().hex[:12]}.{ext}'\n        path = self._cache_dir / filename\n        path.write_bytes(data)\n        return path\n\n    async def cache_from_url(self, url: str, ext: str) -> Path:\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            resp = await client.get(url)\n            resp.raise_for_status()\n        return self.cache_from_bytes(resp.content, ext)\n\nThen create three instances: IMAGE_CACHE = MediaCache('image', 'images'), AUDIO_CACHE = MediaCache('audio', 'audio'), DOCUMENT_CACHE = MediaCache('document', 'documents'). Replace get_image_cache_dir() with IMAGE_CACHE.ensure_dir(), cache_image_from_bytes() with IMAGE_CACHE.cache_from_bytes(), etc. Keep the cleanup functions as standalone \u2014 they have media-type-specific retention logic.",
          "effort": "medium",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Rename the old getters to ensure_cache_dir",
          "detail": "After MediaCache extraction, rename the three wrapper functions to use ensure_* naming: rename get_image_cache_dir -> ensure_image_cache_dir, get_audio_cache_dir -> ensure_audio_cache_dir, get_document_cache_dir -> ensure_document_cache_dir. Check callers outside base.py: grep -rn 'get_image_cache_dir|get_audio_cache_dir|get_document_cache_dir' across all .py files. Update all callers. If MediaCache class is added, these may become internal helpers or can be removed entirely.",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [
            "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::cache_getters_mutate_filesystem"
          ],
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Standardize the exception format inside base.py",
          "detail": "In gateway/platforms/base.py: unify the second parameter in cache_document_from_bytes (uses 'filename: str' at line 205) vs cache_image_from_bytes and cache_audio_from_bytes (use 'ext: str'). Either add optional 'filename' param to image/audio cache functions, or change document function signature to also use 'ext' param (since document names may be auto-generated). Recommend: add optional filename param to MediaCache.cache_from_bytes() so document use case works uniformly.",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "done": true
        }
      ]
    },
    "gateway-config-consolidation": {
      "name": "gateway-config-consolidation",
      "description": "Load config.yaml once via helper in gateway/run.py instead of 20+ independent parses, move module-scope dotenv/YAML loading into _bootstrap_environment(), extract shared load_hermes_env() for .env boilerplate",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::gateway_config_yaml_reload",
        "review::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::gateway_run_import_side_effects",
        "review::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::dotenv_loading_boilerplate"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-03-15T21:14:05+00:00",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-16T02:15:42+00:00",
      "auto": false,
      "cluster_key": "",
      "action": null,
      "action_type": "manual_fix",
      "execution_policy": "planned_only",
      "execution_status": "active",
      "user_modified": true,
      "action_steps": [
        {
          "title": "Add _load_config_yaml() -> dict helper to gateway/run.py that caches config.yaml, replace 11+ inline loads",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "In gateway/run.py: add a module-level helper at line ~455 (before _load_prefill_messages):\n\ndef _load_config_yaml() -> dict:\n    cfg_path = Path.home() / '.hermes' / 'config.yaml'\n    if not cfg_path.exists():\n        return {}\n    with open(cfg_path) as f:\n        return yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n\nThen replace the inline yaml.safe_load pattern at each of these lines with cfg = _load_config_yaml(): lines 463, 501, 522, 1188, 1269, 1772, 1863, 2506, 3269, 3302. Keep the module-scope load at line 53 as-is (it runs at import time for env bridging). Each _load_* method becomes a dict lookup: e.g. _load_prefill_messages changes from open+yaml.safe_load to just _load_config_yaml().get('prefill_messages'). Do NOT cache \u2014 config.yaml may be edited between calls.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Move module-scope dotenv/YAML loading into _bootstrap_environment() called by start_gateway() and GatewayRunner.__init__",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "In gateway/run.py lines 36-44: the module-scope block loads dotenv and bridges config.yaml into env vars. Move lines 36-44 (load_dotenv calls) and lines 46-143 (config.yaml bridging) into a new function:\n\ndef _bootstrap_environment():\n    _env_path = Path.home() / '.hermes' / '.env'\n    if _env_path.exists():\n        try:\n            load_dotenv(_env_path, encoding='utf-8')\n        except UnicodeDecodeError:\n            load_dotenv(_env_path, encoding='latin-1')\n    load_dotenv()\n    # ... move the config.yaml bridging block here ...\n\nThen call _bootstrap_environment() from two places: (1) start_gateway() at the top of its body, (2) GatewayRunner.__init__ at the top. Add a module-level _bootstrapped = False guard so it only runs once. This lets tests import gateway.run without triggering dotenv/YAML side effects.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Extract shared load_hermes_env() helper for .env loading boilerplate used across 7+ files",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "Add load_hermes_env() to hermes_constants.py (file exists at repo root, currently contains only API URL constants \u2014 safe to extend). Add at the bottom:\n\ndef load_hermes_env():\n    from dotenv import load_dotenv\n    from pathlib import Path\n    env_path = Path.home() / '.hermes' / '.env'\n    if env_path.exists():\n        try:\n            load_dotenv(env_path, encoding='utf-8')\n        except UnicodeDecodeError:\n            load_dotenv(env_path, encoding='latin-1')\n    load_dotenv()\n\nThen replace the identical try/except load_dotenv boilerplate in these 5 files with 'from hermes_constants import load_hermes_env; load_hermes_env()': cli.py (lines 70-77), rl_cli.py (lines 39-47), run_agent.py (lines 54-56), gateway/run.py (lines 37-44 \u2014 inside _bootstrap_environment from step 2), mini_swe_runner.py (line 41).",
          "done": true
        }
      ]
    },
    "gateway-run-decomposition": {
      "name": "gateway-run-decomposition",
      "description": "Extract _handle_message phases into _authorize_user, _dispatch_command, _enrich_media, _persist_transcript methods, replace command dispatch if-chain with dispatch dict, add _create_utility_agent factory",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::monolithic_handle_message",
        "review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::ad_hoc_temporary_agent_construction",
        "review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::hasattr_on_init_attributes",
        "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::handle_message_monolith",
        "review::.::holistic::high_level_elegance::monolithic_gateway_run",
        "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::command_dispatch_chain",
        "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::defensive_hasattr_after_init"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-03-15T21:14:08+00:00",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-16T00:37:55+00:00",
      "auto": false,
      "cluster_key": "",
      "action": null,
      "action_type": "manual_fix",
      "execution_policy": "planned_only",
      "execution_status": "active",
      "user_modified": true,
      "action_steps": [
        {
          "title": "Extract _authorize_user, _dispatch_command, _enrich_media, _persist_transcript methods from _handle_message",
          "effort": "medium",
          "issue_refs": [
            "review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::monolithic_handle_message"
          ],
          "detail": "In gateway/run.py _handle_message (lines 912-1629), extract two methods: (1) _handle_unauthorized_user(event, source): extract lines 927-954 (the authorization check + pairing code generation for DMs + silent ignore for groups). Returns bool \u2014 True if authorized, False if handled. Call site becomes: 'if not self._handle_unauthorized_user(event, source): return'. (2) _enrich_media(event, message_text) -> str: extract lines 1405-1470 (image vision enrichment at 1405-1420, audio transcription at 1425-1438, document context at 1443-1470). Returns the enriched message_text. Call site becomes: 'message_text = self._enrich_media(event, message_text)'. Do NOT extract command dispatch or agent launch \u2014 those are tightly coupled to session state.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Replace command dispatch if/elif chain with dispatch dict mapping command strings to handler methods",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "In gateway/run.py: replace the command dispatch at lines 983-1044 with a dispatch dict. Define at class level or inside _handle_message:\n\n_COMMAND_DISPATCH = {\n    'new': '_handle_reset_command', 'reset': '_handle_reset_command',\n    'help': '_handle_help_command', 'status': '_handle_status_command',\n    'stop': '_handle_stop_command', 'model': '_handle_model_command',\n    'provider': '_handle_provider_command', 'personality': '_handle_personality_command',\n    'retry': '_handle_retry_command', 'undo': '_handle_undo_command',\n    'sethome': '_handle_set_home_command', 'set-home': '_handle_set_home_command',\n    'compress': '_handle_compress_command', 'usage': '_handle_usage_command',\n    'insights': '_handle_insights_command',\n    'reload-mcp': '_handle_reload_mcp_command', 'reload_mcp': '_handle_reload_mcp_command',\n    'update': '_handle_update_command', 'title': '_handle_title_command',\n    'resume': '_handle_resume_command', 'rollback': '_handle_rollback_command',\n    'background': '_handle_background_command', 'reasoning': '_handle_reasoning_command',\n    'autoreply': '_handle_autoreply_command',\n}\n\nReplace lines 983-1044 with: handler_name = _COMMAND_DISPATCH.get(command); if handler_name: return await getattr(self, handler_name)(event). Update _known_commands at line 970 to derive from the dict: _known_commands = set(_COMMAND_DISPATCH.keys()). Keep lines 1047-1087 (quick commands, skill commands) as-is.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Add _create_utility_agent factory method to consolidate 4 ad-hoc AIAgent construction sites",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [
            "review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::ad_hoc_temporary_agent_construction",
            "review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::hasattr_on_init_attributes"
          ],
          "detail": "In gateway/run.py: extract a _create_utility_agent method for the 2 utility construction sites that share the same pattern. Sites at line 397 (_async_flush_memories) and line 2596 (_handle_compress_command) both construct: AIAgent(**runtime_kwargs, model=model, max_iterations=N, quiet_mode=True, enabled_toolsets=['memory', ...], session_id=sid). Add method:\n\ndef _create_utility_agent(self, session_id, toolsets, max_iterations=8):\n    model = self._resolve_model()\n    runtime_kwargs = self._build_runtime_kwargs()\n    return AIAgent(**runtime_kwargs, model=model, max_iterations=max_iterations,\n                   quiet_mode=True, enabled_toolsets=toolsets, session_id=session_id)\n\nReplace the AIAgent() calls at lines 397 and 2596 with self._create_utility_agent(). Do NOT touch line 2394 (background command \u2014 has extra params) or line 3557 (main agent \u2014 completely different concern). Also delete the hasattr guards at lines 323-326 in _get_or_create_gateway_honcho \u2014 __init__ at line 257 already initializes _honcho_managers and _honcho_configs.",
          "done": true
        }
      ],
      "depends_on_clusters": [
        "gateway-config-consolidation"
      ]
    },
