    "test-infrastructure": {
      "name": "test-infrastructure",
      "description": "Extract shared _make_runner() fixture to replace object.__new__ pattern in 9 test files, add test_gateway_run.py for core _handle_message dispatch",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::test_strategy::object_new_fragility",
        "review::.::holistic::test_strategy::gateway_run_untested_pipeline"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-03-15T21:14:22+00:00",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-16T02:54:11+00:00",
      "auto": false,
      "cluster_key": "",
      "action": null,
      "action_type": "manual_fix",
      "execution_policy": "planned_only",
      "execution_status": "active",
      "user_modified": true,
      "action_steps": [
        {
          "title": "Extract shared _make_runner() fixture to conftest.py replacing object.__new__ in 9 test files, add test_gateway_run.py for _handle_message dispatch",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "Create tests/gateway/conftest.py (file may already exist \u2014 append if so). Add a _make_runner fixture that replaces object.__new__:\n\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock, AsyncMock\nfrom gateway.run import GatewayRunner\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef make_runner():\n    def _make(**overrides):\n        runner = object.__new__(GatewayRunner)\n        defaults = {\n            'config': MagicMock(), '_session_store': MagicMock(),\n            '_adapters': {}, '_honcho_managers': {}, '_honcho_configs': {},\n            '_session_db': MagicMock(), '_reasoning_config': None,\n            '_prefill_messages': None, '_fallback_model': None,\n            'pairing_store': MagicMock(), 'logger': MagicMock(),\n        }\n        defaults.update(overrides)\n        for attr, val in defaults.items():\n            setattr(runner, attr, val)\n        return runner\n    return _make\n\nThis still uses object.__new__ internally but centralizes attribute setup. The value: when __init__ adds a new attribute, you update ONE fixture instead of 9 test files.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Update 9 test files to use _make_runner() fixture instead of object.__new__",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "Update these test files to use the conftest make_runner fixture instead of inline object.__new__ + manual attribute setup: tests/gateway/test_background_command.py (line 31), tests/gateway/test_session_hygiene.py (line 264), tests/gateway/test_honcho_lifecycle.py (line 16). In each file: (1) add 'make_runner' as a test function parameter, (2) replace 'runner = object.__new__(GatewayRunner)' + the following setattr lines with 'runner = make_runner()'. Pass overrides for test-specific attributes, e.g. make_runner(_session_store=my_mock_store). Search for other files: grep -rn 'object.__new__(GatewayRunner)' tests/ to find all 9 \u2014 update each the same way.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Add test_gateway_run.py with command dispatch routing tests",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "Create tests/gateway/test_gateway_run.py with 3 command dispatch tests using the make_runner fixture:\n\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, MagicMock, patch\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_help_command_dispatches(make_runner):\n    runner = make_runner()\n    runner._handle_help_command = AsyncMock()\n    event = MagicMock(text='/help', media_urls=[], source=MagicMock())\n    event.source.session_key = 'test-session'\n    with patch.object(runner, '_is_user_authorized', return_value=True):\n        await runner._handle_message(event)\n    runner._handle_help_command.assert_called_once()\n\nWrite similar tests for /model and /stop commands. Each test: create runner via make_runner(), mock the specific handler, create a minimal event with text='/command', patch _is_user_authorized to return True, call _handle_message, assert the handler was called. Do NOT test agent launch or media enrichment \u2014 those need integration-level setup.",
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Add test_gateway_run.py agent launch and error path tests",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "detail": "In tests/gateway/test_gateway_run.py: add 2 error path tests:\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_unauthorized_user_gets_pairing_code(make_runner):\n    runner = make_runner(pairing_store=MagicMock(generate_code=MagicMock(return_value='ABC123')))\n    event = MagicMock(text='hello', media_urls=[], source=MagicMock(is_dm=True))\n    with patch.object(runner, '_is_user_authorized', return_value=False):\n        with patch.object(runner, '_send_response', new_callable=AsyncMock) as send:\n            await runner._handle_message(event)\n            send.assert_called_once()\n            assert 'ABC123' in str(send.call_args)\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_unknown_command_falls_through(make_runner):\n    runner = make_runner()\n    event = MagicMock(text='/nonexistent', media_urls=[], source=MagicMock())\n    with patch.object(runner, '_is_user_authorized', return_value=True):\n        with patch.object(runner, '_run_agent', new_callable=AsyncMock):\n            await runner._handle_message(event)\n            # Should fall through to agent, not crash\n            runner._run_agent.assert_called_once()\n\nThese test the authorization gate and unknown-command fallthrough. Adjust method names (_send_response, _run_agent) to match actual names \u2014 grep for 'async def _send' and 'async def _run_agent' in gateway/run.py.",
          "done": true
        }
      ],
      "depends_on_clusters": [
        "gateway-config-consolidation"
      ]
    },
    "error-consistency": {
      "name": "error-consistency",
      "description": "Fix mixed logging and session DB error visibility",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::mixed_logging_for_errors",
        "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::session_db_errors_invisible"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-03-15T23:02:46+00:00",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-15T23:51:04+00:00",
      "auto": false,
      "cluster_key": "",
      "action": null,
      "action_type": "manual_fix",
      "execution_policy": "planned_only",
      "execution_status": "active",
      "user_modified": true,
      "action_steps": [
        {
          "title": "Standardize logging",
          "detail": "Overlaps with gateway-session-improvements step 1. In gateway/session.py: replace all print() calls (lines 350, 367, 562) with logger.warning(). In gateway/platforms/base.py: check for any print() error reporting and replace with logger. Both files verified: session.py has print() at lines 350, 367, 562 confirmed present.",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Use warning instead of debug",
          "detail": "In gateway/session.py: promote logger.debug() DB failure calls to logger.warning(). Affected lines: 531, 562, 592, 608, 636, 664, 721, 748, 765 (all 'Session DB operation failed' debug messages). Change to logger.warning() since DB failures are operationally significant. Do NOT change line 279 (Unknown platform value) \u2014 that's already debug-appropriate.",
          "effort": "trivial",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "done": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Catch explicit exceptions",
          "detail": "In gateway/session.py: change 'except Exception' to 'except sqlite3.Error' at lines 349, 366, 491, 530, 561, 591, 607, 635, 663, 720, 747, 764. These are all DB operation handlers and should only catch sqlite3 errors, not all exceptions. Import sqlite3 is already present in session.py. Check: does session.py import sqlite3? Verified: grep shows sqlite3.Error is not used yet, only 'except Exception'.",
          "effort": "small",
          "issue_refs": [],
          "done": true
        }
      ],
      "depends_on_clusters": [
        "gateway-session-improvements"
      ]
    }
  },
