    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:30:29+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::triplicated_cache_utilities"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "Over-engineered: extracting a MediaCache class for 3 instances of <30 lines each adds abstraction for marginal dedup. Current flat functions are self-contained and clear.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:30:31+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::media_cache_triplication"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "Over-engineered: same issue as triplicated_cache_utilities. The proposed class hierarchy adds indirection for 3 straightforward copy-paste variants.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:30:38+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::naming_quality::do_prefix_skills_hub"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "Renaming 11 do_* functions in skills_hub.py is pure naming churn \u2014 the do_ prefix is a clear convention for CLI action handlers, no ambiguity exists, and the rename touches every call site for zero functional benefit.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:30:41+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::aiagent_wide_constructor"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "Over-engineered: introducing ProviderConfig/CallbackConfig dataclasses for AIAgent.__init__ adds 2 new types, requires updating 5+ call sites, and trades one form of sprawl (many params) for another (config objects that must be constructed). The params are already typed and grouped by convention in the signature.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:30:43+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::aiagent_init_parameter_sprawl"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "Same as aiagent_wide_constructor \u2014 the proposed ProviderConfig/CallbackConfig dataclasses add more indirection than they remove, and all 5 call sites would need refactoring for marginal benefit.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:30:51+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::command_dispatch_chain"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "The if/elif command dispatch chain (lines 983-1070 in gateway/run.py) is straightforward, each branch is 1 line, and replacing it with a dispatch dict + getattr adds indirection without improving readability. The chain is easy to extend and grep-able.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:30:58+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::tools_import_cli_config"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "Over-engineered: changing 2 tool files to receive config via kwargs requires modifying the tool dispatch in model_tools.py, which is a wider change than the problem warrants. The current from cli import CLI_CONFIG fallback pattern works fine and is encapsulated in _load_config() helpers.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:31:00+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::private_symbols_crossed_across_boundaries"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "Promoting private symbols to public API by removing underscores is a naming convention change with no functional benefit. The symbols work fine as-is, and renaming them would change the public API surface without necessity.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:31:03+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::bidirectional_root_hermes_cli_coupling"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "Massive refactor: extracting CLI_CONFIG into a dedicated config/state module and moving model_tools.py requires touching 24+ import edges across the codebase. This is a high-risk architectural change with no clear correctness benefit \u2014 the current coupling is functional.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:31:06+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::gateway_tools_bidirectional_coupling"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "Moving GATEWAY_SECRET_CAPTURE_UNSUPPORTED_MESSAGE to hermes_constants.py is trivial in isolation but the rest of the bidirectional coupling fix (inject gateway deps into tools) is a large refactor. The constant is a single string used in one place; moving it doesn't solve the architectural issue.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-15T21:31:18+00:00",
      "action": "skip",
      "issue_ids": [
        "review::.::holistic::incomplete_migration::sqlite_jsonl_dual_write"
      ],
      "cluster_name": null,
      "actor": "user",
      "note": "Step only adds TODO comments to code. Adding comments about a future migration path is not cleanup \u2014 the dual-write is intentional during migration and already documented in the docstring 'keeps existing tooling working during transition'.",
      "detail": {
        "kind": "permanent",
        "reason": null
      }
    },
