      "stages": {
        "observe": {
          "stage": "observe",
          "report": "# OBSERVE Stage Report \u2014 hermes-agent (New Triage Run)\nAll 35 open review issues verified against source code. Full issue IDs cited for each issue.\n\n## Structured Assessments\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::tools_init_redundant_barrel\n  hash: tools_init_redundant_barrel\n  verdict: not-worth-it\n  verdict_reasoning: tools/__init__.py re-exports 81+ symbols. Registry-based discovery handles tool loading for model_tools.py. The barrel provides backward compatibility. Removing it is a breaking change without clear benefit.\n  files_read: [tools/__init__.py]\n  recommendation: Keep as-is unless registry-based discovery is adopted holistically.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::dotenv_loading_boilerplate\n  hash: dotenv_loading_boilerplate\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: cli.py lines 62-77, run_agent.py lines 47-60, and gateway/run.py lines 36-44 all have identical try/except UnicodeDecodeError load_dotenv pattern. Confirmed duplication across 3 entry points.\n  files_read: [cli.py, run_agent.py, gateway/run.py]\n  recommendation: Extract to a shared hermes_env.load() function in hermes_constants.py.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::stale_probability_comments\n  hash: stale_probability_comments\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed in toolset_distributions.py lines 48-50: \"image_gen\": 90 # 80% chance, \"vision\": 90 # 60% chance. Lines 201-202: \"web\": 97 # 15% chance. Values and comments contradict each other.\n  files_read: [toolset_distributions.py]\n  recommendation: Remove percentage comments or update them to match actual values.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::toolsets_docstring_bloat\n  hash: toolsets_docstring_bloat\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed in toolsets.py: get_toolset() is a one-liner (return TOOLSETS.get(name)) with a 10-line Args/Returns docstring. Same pattern for get_all_toolsets(), get_toolset_names(), validate_toolset().\n  files_read: [toolsets.py]\n  recommendation: Trim docstrings to one-line summaries.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::toolsets_restating_comments\n  hash: toolsets_restating_comments\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed in toolsets.py lines 311, 342, 349, 354: comments like # Return toolset definition above return TOOLSETS.get(name) purely restate the code.\n  files_read: [toolsets.py]\n  recommendation: Delete the restating comments.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::authorization_consistency::allowlist_env_var_magic_strings\n  hash: allowlist_env_var_magic_strings\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_USERS, DISCORD_ALLOWED_USERS, SLACK_ALLOWED_USERS, WHATSAPP_ALLOWED_USERS appear as string literals in gateway/run.py lines 632-634 and 865-868, hermes_cli/setup.py lines 1876/1955/2045, hermes_cli/gateway.py lines 443/471/504.\n  files_read: [gateway/run.py, hermes_cli/setup.py, hermes_cli/gateway.py, gateway/platforms/discord.py]\n  recommendation: Define as constants in gateway/config.py and import everywhere.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::cache_getters_mutate_filesystem\n  hash: cache_getters_mutate_filesystem\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: get_image_cache_dir() line 49, get_audio_cache_dir() line 131, get_document_cache_dir() line 199 in gateway/platforms/base.py all call .mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True). The get_ prefix implies pure read.\n  files_read: [gateway/platforms/base.py]\n  recommendation: Rename to ensure_image_cache_dir() or separate the mkdir into an explicit init.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::deliver_returns_sendresult_not_dict\n  hash: deliver_returns_sendresult_not_dict\n  verdict: exaggerated\n  verdict_reasoning: _deliver_to_platform line 269 annotated -> Dict[str, Any] but returns SendResult dataclass. The caller at line 195 wraps it: {\"success\": True, \"result\": result}. Annotation mismatch is real but doesn't cause runtime errors.\n  files_read: [gateway/delivery.py, gateway/platforms/base.py]\n  recommendation: Fix the private method annotation to -> SendResult.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::toolset_info_returns_none\n  hash: toolset_info_returns_none\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: toolsets.py line 446 declares -> Dict[str, Any], line 458 returns None when toolset not found. A caller doing info[\"name\"] on the result would get AttributeError.\n  files_read: [toolsets.py]\n  recommendation: Change annotation to -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]].\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::convention_outlier::check_ha_requirements_naming\n  hash: check_ha_requirements_naming\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: homeassistant.py has def check_ha_requirements() while every other adapter uses the full platform name: check_telegram_requirements, check_discord_requirements, etc.\n  files_read: [gateway/platforms/homeassistant.py]\n  recommendation: Rename to check_homeassistant_requirements. One-line change.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::convention_outlier::large_tools_init_barrel\n  hash: large_tools_init_barrel\n  verdict: not-worth-it\n  verdict_reasoning: tools/__init__.py is 264 lines re-exporting 81+ symbols. Consumers bypass it via direct imports, but the barrel still provides a public API surface. Removing it is a breaking change without clear benefit.\n  files_read: [tools/__init__.py]\n  recommendation: Keep as-is unless registry-based discovery is adopted holistically.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::convention_outlier::platform_sys_path_split\n  hash: platform_sys_path_split\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: telegram.py, discord.py, slack.py, whatsapp.py all have sys.path.insert(0,...). signal.py, email.py, homeassistant.py do not \u2014 they import from gateway.config directly. All are siblings in the same directory.\n  files_read: [gateway/platforms/telegram.py, gateway/platforms/discord.py, gateway/platforms/signal.py, gateway/platforms/homeassistant.py]\n  recommendation: Standardize \u2014 either all use sys.path.insert or none do.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::registry_violates_own_contract\n  hash: registry_violates_own_contract\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: tools/registry.py line 8 of the docstring explicitly states \"no imports from model_tools or tool files\", yet line 124 has from model_tools import _run_async as a deferred import in the async bridging path. Contradiction is real and verified.\n  files_read: [tools/registry.py]\n  recommendation: Either remove the contradicting docstring line or refactor to remove the private import.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::dependency_health::dual_http_clients\n  hash: dual_http_clients\n  verdict: not-worth-it\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: requests is used in only 2 files (browser_tool.py, model_metadata.py) while httpx is used in 4+ files. Dual usage is real but requests is used in simple synchronous contexts. Migrating 2 files is low-risk but marginal benefit.\n  files_read: [tools/browser_tool.py, agent/model_metadata.py]\n  recommendation: Migrate in a future cleanup pass. Not a priority.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::dependency_health::orphaned_mini_swe_deps\n  hash: orphaned_mini_swe_deps\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: mini-swe-agent/ directory is empty. litellm, typer, platformdirs in pyproject.toml lines 34-36 with a \"# mini-swe-agent deps\" comment. Zero import sites found across all .py files.\n  files_read: [pyproject.toml, requirements.txt]\n  recommendation: Remove litellm, typer, platformdirs from core deps.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::dependency_health::requirements_txt_drift\n  hash: requirements_txt_drift\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: requirements.txt includes python-telegram-bot>=20.0, discord.py>=2.0, aiohttp>=3.9.0 as core deps while pyproject.toml correctly puts these in [messaging] optional extras.\n  files_read: [requirements.txt, pyproject.toml]\n  recommendation: Regenerate requirements.txt from pyproject.toml or audit for drift regularly.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::dependency_health::unused_jinja2_dep\n  hash: unused_jinja2_dep\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: jinja2 is in pyproject.toml line 24 as a core dependency. Zero import sites found across all .py files.\n  files_read: [pyproject.toml, requirements.txt]\n  recommendation: Remove jinja2 from core dependencies.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::design_coherence::gateway_config_yaml_reload\n  hash: gateway_config_yaml_reload\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: gateway/run.py has 20+ independent yaml.safe_load() call sites confirmed at lines 51, 200, 459, 497, 518, 541, 564, 590, 608, 1188, 1772, 1863, 1894, 1907, 1956, 2222, 2365, 2506, 3269, 3302. Each _load_* static method independently opens and parses config.yaml.\n  files_read: [gateway/run.py]\n  recommendation: Introduce a _load_config() method that parses once, eliminating repeated I/O.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::error_consistency::mixed_logging_for_errors\n  hash: mixed_logging_for_errors\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: gateway/session.py uses print() at lines 350, 367, 562 despite having a logger. gateway/platforms/base.py uses print() at lines 669, 672, 737, 746, 815, 817, 822, 836 while using logger.error() at lines 775, 777.\n  files_read: [gateway/session.py, gateway/platforms/base.py]\n  recommendation: Replace print() calls with logger.warning()/logger.error() calls.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::error_consistency::session_db_errors_invisible\n  hash: session_db_errors_invisible\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: gateway/session.py has 12 except blocks for SQLite operations (lines 349, 366, 491, 530, 561, 591, 607, 635, 663, 720, 747, 764) all logging at debug level. Database corruption would be invisible in production.\n  files_read: [gateway/session.py]\n  recommendation: Elevate DB open failure to logger.warning and per-operation failures to logger.warning on first occurrence.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::high_level_elegance::agents_md_structure_drift\n  hash: agents_md_structure_drift\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: AGENTS.md line 57 references acp_adapter/ which does not exist in the repository (confirmed by ls). Numerous real directories (honcho_integration/, skills/, demo/) and files are absent from the documented structure.\n  files_read: [AGENTS.md]\n  recommendation: Update AGENTS.md to reflect the actual directory tree.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::gateway_run_import_side_effects\n  hash: gateway_run_import_side_effects\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: gateway/run.py lines 36-99 perform dotenv loading, config.yaml parsing, and os.environ mutation at module scope. Any test that imports GatewayRunner gets file I/O and env pollution. Root cause of object.__new__ test fragility.\n  files_read: [gateway/run.py]\n  recommendation: Move module-scope initialization behind a function or lazy initialization.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::model_tools_stale_snapshots\n  hash: model_tools_stale_snapshots\n  verdict: exaggerated\n  verdict_reasoning: model_tools.py lines 122-124 build TOOL_TO_TOOLSET_MAP and TOOLSET_REQUIREMENTS at module level after _discover_tools(). Dynamic post-import tool registration doesn't happen in this codebase's current design. Theoretically valid but overstates practical risk.\n  files_read: [model_tools.py]\n  recommendation: Document the assumption. Low priority.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::sys_path_insert_gateway_modules\n  hash: sys_path_insert_gateway_modules\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: gateway/platforms/base.py line 24, telegram.py line 48, discord.py line 31, whatsapp.py line 66, slack.py line 30 all have sys.path.insert(0,...). Each import adds a duplicate entry.\n  files_read: [gateway/platforms/base.py, gateway/platforms/telegram.py, gateway/platforms/discord.py]\n  recommendation: Fix package structure so sys.path manipulation is unnecessary.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::ad_hoc_temporary_agent_construction\n  hash: ad_hoc_temporary_agent_construction\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed in gateway/run.py: _flush_memories_for_session, _handle_compress_command, session hygiene, and _run_agent each independently construct AIAgent instances with different parameter sets and error handling.\n  files_read: [gateway/run.py]\n  recommendation: Introduce a factory method _build_temporary_agent(max_iterations, toolsets).\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::hasattr_on_init_attributes\n  hash: hasattr_on_init_attributes\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Lines 323-326 of gateway/run.py: if not hasattr(self, \"_honcho_managers\"): self._honcho_managers = {} \u2014 but __init__ on line 257 already initializes this attribute unconditionally. The hasattr guards are dead code.\n  files_read: [gateway/run.py]\n  recommendation: Remove the hasattr guards.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::monolithic_handle_message\n  hash: monolithic_handle_message\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Verified _handle_message in gateway/run.py combines authorization, interrupt detection, 20+ if/elif command dispatch, media enrichment, agent launch, transcript persistence, and autoreply scheduling all in one inline flow.\n  files_read: [gateway/run.py]\n  recommendation: Extract sub-concerns into collaborator methods or a command dispatcher object.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::scattered_config_yaml_parsing\n  hash: scattered_config_yaml_parsing\n  verdict: exaggerated\n  verdict_reasoning: Same underlying issue as gateway_config_yaml_reload \u2014 both describe repeated yaml.safe_load in gateway/run.py. The issue is real but triple-counted alongside repeated_config_yaml_loading and gateway_config_yaml_reload.\n  files_read: [gateway/run.py]\n  recommendation: Merge with gateway_config_yaml_reload. Fix once.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::test_strategy::gateway_run_untested_pipeline\n  hash: gateway_run_untested_pipeline\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: gateway/run.py is the central orchestrator. Individual command tests exist but the _handle_message dispatch pipeline, authorization paths, and agent invocation chain have no dedicated test coverage.\n  files_read: [gateway/run.py, tests/gateway/]\n  recommendation: Fix gateway_run_import_side_effects first to enable proper testing, then add pipeline tests.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::test_strategy::object_new_fragility\n  hash: object_new_fragility\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: 9 test files in tests/gateway/ use object.__new__(GatewayRunner) and manually set 8-12 internal attributes. test_autoreply_command.py shows the pattern at lines 35-70. Directly caused by gateway_run_import_side_effects.\n  files_read: [tests/gateway/test_autoreply_command.py, tests/gateway/test_honcho_lifecycle.py, tests/gateway/test_control_api.py, tests/gateway/test_session_hygiene.py]\n  recommendation: Fix gateway_run_import_side_effects first, then refactor tests to use a proper factory/fixture.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::type_safety::adapters_dict_any_any\n  hash: adapters_dict_any_any\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: gateway/channel_directory.py line 44 build_channel_directory(adapters: Dict[Any, Any]) but line 56 immediately compares keys against Platform enum values.\n  files_read: [gateway/channel_directory.py]\n  recommendation: Change to Dict[Platform, Any].\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::type_safety::message_event_source_not_optional\n  hash: message_event_source_not_optional\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: gateway/platforms/base.py line 283 source: SessionSource = None. Callers at lines 706-707 access event.source.thread_id and event.source.chat_id without null checks.\n  files_read: [gateway/platforms/base.py]\n  recommendation: Change annotation to Optional[SessionSource] = None and audit callers.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::type_safety::optional_without_annotation\n  hash: optional_without_annotation\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed in run_agent.py lines 215-249: base_url: str = None, api_key: str = None, api_mode: str = None, max_tokens: int = None, tool_progress_callback: callable = None. Same pattern in gateway/session.py line 571 and gateway/pairing.py line 95.\n  files_read: [run_agent.py, gateway/session.py, gateway/pairing.py]\n  recommendation: Add Optional[] wrappers. Mechanical fix.\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::type_safety::untyped_discriminator_api_mode\n  hash: untyped_discriminator_api_mode\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: run_agent.py line 218 api_mode: str = None, only valid as 3 values. 50+ comparison sites. run_agent.py:321 validates against a set literal but discards the constraint into a bare str field.\n  files_read: [run_agent.py]\n  recommendation: Define ApiMode = Literal[\"chat_completions\", \"codex_responses\", \"anthropic_messages\"].\n\n- issue_id: review::.::holistic::type_safety::untyped_discriminator_reset_mode\n  hash: untyped_discriminator_reset_mode\n  verdict: genuine\n  verdict_reasoning: Confirmed: gateway/config.py line 73 mode: str = \"both\". gateway/session.py has 6 comparison sites against string literals with no typo protection.\n  files_read: [gateway/config.py, gateway/session.py]\n  recommendation: Use Literal[\"daily\", \"idle\", \"both\", \"none\"] for the mode field.\n\n## Auto-Cluster Sample Checks\n\n- cluster: auto/test_coverage\n  verdict: actionable\n  sample_count: 5\n  false_positive_rate: 0.2\n  recommendation: promote\n\n- cluster: auto/unused_enums\n  verdict: mixed\n  sample_count: 2\n  false_positive_rate: 1.0\n  recommendation: skip\n",
