          "report": "## Coverage Ledger\n\nAuto-skipped (exaggerated verdict \u2014 no ledger entry per instructions):\n- review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::scattered_config_yaml_parsing \u2014 auto-skipped (exaggerated)\n- review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::repeated_config_yaml_loading \u2014 auto-skipped (exaggerated)\n- review::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::model_tools_stale_snapshots \u2014 auto-skipped (exaggerated)\n- review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::deliver_returns_sendresult_not_dict \u2014 auto-skipped (exaggerated)\n\nLedger (41 entries, covering all remaining active_triage_issue_ids plus 2 auto-cluster items):\n\nreview::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::registry_violates_own_contract -> cluster \"cross-module-import-hygiene\"\nreview::.::holistic::high_level_elegance::agents_md_structure_drift -> cluster \"docs-and-misc-fixes\"\nreview::.::holistic::design_coherence::gateway_config_yaml_reload -> cluster \"gateway-config-consolidation\"\nreview::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::monolithic_handle_message -> cluster \"gateway-run-decomposition\"\nreview::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::ad_hoc_temporary_agent_construction -> cluster \"gateway-run-decomposition\"\nreview::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::hasattr_on_init_attributes -> cluster \"gateway-run-decomposition\"\nreview::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::patch_parser_duplicated_flush -> cluster \"dead-code-and-logic-fixes\"\nreview::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::defensive_hasattr_after_init -> cluster \"gateway-run-decomposition\"\nreview::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::toolsets_docstring_bloat -> cluster \"toolsets-ai-debt-cleanup\"\nreview::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::toolsets_restating_comments -> cluster \"toolsets-ai-debt-cleanup\"\nreview::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::stale_probability_comments -> cluster \"toolsets-ai-debt-cleanup\"\nreview::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::dotenv_loading_boilerplate -> cluster \"gateway-config-consolidation\"\nreview::.::holistic::convention_outlier::platform_sys_path_split -> cluster \"cross-module-import-hygiene\"\nreview::.::holistic::convention_outlier::check_ha_requirements_naming -> cluster \"gateway-naming-conventions\"\nreview::.::holistic::convention_outlier::large_tools_init_barrel -> skip \"not-worth-it: removing is a breaking change for external consumers with no clear benefit; duplicates tools_init_redundant_barrel\"\nreview::.::holistic::authorization_consistency::allowlist_env_var_magic_strings -> cluster \"gateway-naming-conventions\"\nreview::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::gateway_run_import_side_effects -> cluster \"gateway-config-consolidation\"\nreview::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::sys_path_insert_gateway_modules -> cluster \"cross-module-import-hygiene\"\nreview::.::holistic::contract_coherence::toolset_info_returns_none -> cluster \"type-safety-annotations\"\nreview::.::holistic::contract_coherence::cache_getters_mutate_filesystem -> cluster \"gateway-platform-base-cleanup\"\nreview::.::holistic::logic_clarity::identical_branches_telegram_document -> cluster \"dead-code-and-logic-fixes\"\nreview::.::holistic::logic_clarity::identical_branches_uninstall -> cluster \"dead-code-and-logic-fixes\"\nreview::.::holistic::logic_clarity::identical_branches_skills_sync -> cluster \"dead-code-and-logic-fixes\"\nreview::.::holistic::logic_clarity::dead_code_checkpoint_manager -> cluster \"dead-code-and-logic-fixes\"\nreview::.::holistic::logic_clarity::duplicated_dead_countdown_check -> cluster \"dead-code-and-logic-fixes\"\nreview::.::holistic::type_safety::optional_without_annotation -> cluster \"type-safety-annotations\"\nreview::.::holistic::type_safety::untyped_discriminator_api_mode -> cluster \"type-safety-annotations\"\nreview::.::holistic::type_safety::untyped_discriminator_reset_mode -> cluster \"type-safety-annotations\"\nreview::.::holistic::type_safety::message_event_source_not_optional -> cluster \"type-safety-annotations\"\nreview::.::holistic::type_safety::adapters_dict_any_any -> cluster \"type-safety-annotations\"\nreview::.::holistic::dependency_health::unused_jinja2_dep -> cluster \"dependency-cleanup\"\nreview::.::holistic::dependency_health::orphaned_mini_swe_deps -> cluster \"dependency-cleanup\"\nreview::.::holistic::dependency_health::dual_http_clients -> skip \"not-worth-it: requests used in only 2 synchronous contexts; migration is low-risk but marginal benefit\"\nreview::.::holistic::dependency_health::requirements_txt_drift -> cluster \"dependency-cleanup\"\nreview::.::holistic::incomplete_migration::deprecated_on_auto_reset_param -> cluster \"gateway-session-improvements\"\nreview::.::holistic::incomplete_migration::deprecated_env_var_still_read -> cluster \"gateway-session-improvements\"\nreview::.::holistic::test_strategy::gateway_run_untested_pipeline -> cluster \"test-infrastructure\"\nreview::.::holistic::test_strategy::object_new_fragility -> cluster \"test-infrastructure\"\nreview::.::holistic::error_consistency::mixed_logging_for_errors -> cluster \"error-consistency\"\nreview::.::holistic::error_consistency::session_db_errors_invisible -> cluster \"error-consistency\"\nreview::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::tools_init_redundant_barrel -> skip \"not-worth-it: barrel provides backward-compat public API surface; removing is a breaking change without measurable benefit\"\nunused_enums::tests/tools/test_daytona_environment.py::_SandboxState -> skip \"false positive confirmed in observe: _SandboxState IS used as mock module attribute replacement at line 43\"\nunused_enums::tools/skills_tool.py::SkillReadinessStatus -> skip \"false positive confirmed in observe: SkillReadinessStatus IS used extensively at lines 401, 405, 887, 1122, 1124, 1139\"\n\n## Cluster Blueprint\n\n### dead-code-and-logic-fixes\n**Thesis:** Six verified instances of dead/duplicate code across unrelated files. Each is a mechanical deletion or collapse \u2014 no design changes needed. Cluster by fix type (dead code), not by file.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::dead_code_checkpoint_manager (tools/checkpoint_manager.py lines 255-260: dead git call immediately overwritten)\n- review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::duplicated_dead_countdown_check (cli.py lines 3549-3551: second countdown refresh check always False)\n- review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::identical_branches_telegram_document (telegram.py lines 736-739: elif and else both assign DOCUMENT)\n- review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::identical_branches_uninstall (uninstall.py lines 278-286: both branches identical)\n- review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::identical_branches_skills_sync (skills_sync.py lines 204-208: both branches do skipped += 1)\n- review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::patch_parser_duplicated_flush (patch_parser.py: flush guard block repeated 4x)\n\n### toolsets-ai-debt-cleanup\n**Thesis:** Three AI-generated debt patterns in toolsets.py and toolset_distributions.py. Docstring bloat, restating comments, and contradicted probability comments are all in the same 2 files. Cluster for one PR.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::toolsets_docstring_bloat (toolsets.py: 10-line docstrings on 1-liner functions)\n- review::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::toolsets_restating_comments (toolsets.py: comments restate the code)\n- review::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::stale_probability_comments (toolset_distributions.py: values contradict comment percentages)\n\n### type-safety-annotations\n**Thesis:** Five mechanical Optional/Literal annotation fixes plus one return type fix, all addressing the same class of issue: Python typing is not reflecting actual nullable or enumerated semantics. Root cause is the same across all: parameters that can be None are not annotated Optional, and string discriminators lack Literal types.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::type_safety::optional_without_annotation (run_agent.py, gateway/session.py, gateway/pairing.py: str = None not annotated Optional)\n- review::.::holistic::type_safety::untyped_discriminator_api_mode (run_agent.py: api_mode is Literal of 3 values, not bare str)\n- review::.::holistic::type_safety::untyped_discriminator_reset_mode (gateway/config.py: mode is Literal of 4 values, not bare str)\n- review::.::holistic::type_safety::message_event_source_not_optional (gateway/platforms/base.py: source: SessionSource = None not Optional)\n- review::.::holistic::type_safety::adapters_dict_any_any (gateway/channel_directory.py: Dict[Any,Any] should be Dict[Platform, Any])\n- review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::toolset_info_returns_none (toolsets.py: return type Dict not Optional[Dict])\n\n### dependency-cleanup\n**Thesis:** Three confirmed unused/drifted dependency issues in pyproject.toml and requirements.txt. jinja2 and mini-swe-agent deps are orphaned dead weight; requirements.txt incorrectly promotes optional messaging deps to core.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::dependency_health::unused_jinja2_dep (pyproject.toml: jinja2 in core deps, zero import sites)\n- review::.::holistic::dependency_health::orphaned_mini_swe_deps (pyproject.toml: litellm/typer/platformdirs with mini-swe comment, zero import sites)\n- review::.::holistic::dependency_health::requirements_txt_drift (requirements.txt includes optional messaging deps as core)\n\n### gateway-platform-base-cleanup\n**Thesis:** cache getter methods in gateway/platforms/base.py violate naming contract by mutating filesystem. Renaming or restructuring these 3 methods fixes the contract mismatch.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::cache_getters_mutate_filesystem (base.py: get_image/audio/document_cache_dir all call mkdir)\n\n### gateway-config-consolidation\n**Thesis:** The root configuration loading problem in gateway/run.py: 20+ yaml.safe_load() call sites at module scope cause repeated I/O, test pollution from import side-effects, and the dotenv_loading_boilerplate pattern is duplicated across 3 entry points. The gateway_run_import_side_effects is the prerequisite for the test-infrastructure cluster. All 4 issues share the same file (gateway/run.py) and the same fix: centralize config loading.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::design_coherence::gateway_config_yaml_reload (gateway/run.py: 20+ yaml.safe_load call sites)\n- review::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::gateway_run_import_side_effects (gateway/run.py: dotenv + config parsing at module scope)\n- review::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::dotenv_loading_boilerplate (cli.py, run_agent.py, gateway/run.py: identical try/except load_dotenv)\n\n### gateway-run-decomposition\n**Thesis:** gateway/run.py GatewayRunner class has three related elegance issues that share root cause: the class does too much inline. _handle_message is a 20+ branch monolith, ad_hoc agent construction is scattered, and hasattr guards exist for attributes already initialized in __init__. All fixes are in gateway/run.py and together represent decomposing the monolith.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::monolithic_handle_message (gateway/run.py: authorization + dispatch + media + agent + autoreply all inline)\n- review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::ad_hoc_temporary_agent_construction (gateway/run.py: AIAgent constructed independently in 4 places)\n- review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::hasattr_on_init_attributes (gateway/run.py lines 323-326: hasattr guards for __init__-set attributes)\n- review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::defensive_hasattr_after_init (gateway/run.py: same pattern as hasattr_on_init_attributes, duplicated in _shutdown_gateway_honcho)\n\n### gateway-session-improvements\n**Thesis:** Two incomplete migration remnants in gateway/session.py and gateway/run.py: a deprecated parameter still in the signature (on_auto_reset), and a deprecated env var still read in run.py after migration code exists in hermes_cli/config.py.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::incomplete_migration::deprecated_on_auto_reset_param (gateway/session.py line 334: parameter not used, should be removed)\n- review::.::holistic::incomplete_migration::deprecated_env_var_still_read (gateway/run.py line 3308: HERMES_TOOL_PROGRESS_MODE fallback undermines migration)\n\n### cross-module-import-hygiene\n**Thesis:** Three verified issues share the same root cause: sys.path manipulation is used because the package structure doesn't enable proper relative imports. This spans gateway/platforms/ (4 files have sys.path.insert, 3 don't) and tools/registry.py (undocumented private import from model_tools). The fix is to establish proper package structure.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::convention_outlier::platform_sys_path_split (telegram/discord/slack/whatsapp have sys.path.insert; signal/email/homeassistant don't)\n- review::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::sys_path_insert_gateway_modules (gateway/platforms/base.py + 4 adapters all add sys.path entries)\n- review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::registry_violates_own_contract (tools/registry.py: docstring says no model_tools imports, line 124 has one)\n\n### gateway-naming-conventions\n**Thesis:** Two naming/constant issues that share the fix pattern of defining string constants properly: allowlist env var names scattered as magic strings, and a function named inconsistently with its peers.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::authorization_consistency::allowlist_env_var_magic_strings (TELEGRAM/DISCORD/SLACK/WHATSAPP_ALLOWED_USERS repeated as literals across 4 files)\n- review::.::holistic::convention_outlier::check_ha_requirements_naming (homeassistant.py: check_ha_requirements vs check_X_requirements pattern)\n\n### docs-and-misc-fixes\n**Thesis:** Single documentation drift issue \u2014 AGENTS.md references a non-existent directory and is missing real directories. Straightforward update.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::high_level_elegance::agents_md_structure_drift (AGENTS.md references acp_adapter/ which doesn't exist)\n\n### test-infrastructure\n**Thesis:** The 9 test files using object.__new__(GatewayRunner) are directly caused by gateway_run_import_side_effects making GatewayRunner un-instantiable in tests. Fix the root cause (gateway-config-consolidation) first, then refactor all 9 test files to use a proper factory.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::test_strategy::object_new_fragility (9 test files use object.__new__ with manual attribute injection)\n- review::.::holistic::test_strategy::gateway_run_untested_pipeline (_handle_message dispatch pipeline has no dedicated test coverage)\n\n### error-consistency\n**Thesis:** Two error logging issues in the same subsystem (gateway/session.py and gateway/platforms/base.py): print() mixed with logger.error(), and SQLite failures logged at debug instead of warning.\n**Issues:**\n- review::.::holistic::error_consistency::mixed_logging_for_errors (gateway/session.py and base.py: print() calls where logger exists)\n- review::.::holistic::error_consistency::session_db_errors_invisible (gateway/session.py: 12 SQLite except blocks at debug level)\n\n## Backlog Decisions\n\nauto/test_coverage -> promote: 61-item cluster is 80% genuine (4/5 sample verified), covers untested critical modules (web_research_env.py 715 lines, mini_swe_runner.py) with no false positives on untested_module/untested_critical categories. transitive_only subcategory has borderline items but still valid.\nauto/unused_enums -> skip: both items are false positives confirmed by reading source code; _SandboxState IS used as mock assignment, SkillReadinessStatus IS used at 6+ call sites.\nauto/unused -> skip: empty cluster with 0 issues.\nauto/security -> skip: empty cluster with 0 issues.\nauto/initial-review -> skip: empty cluster with 0 issues.\n\n## Skip Decisions\n\n- review::.::holistic::convention_outlier::large_tools_init_barrel: not-worth-it \u2014 barrel provides backward-compat public API; removing is breaking without clear benefit; duplicated concern with tools_init_redundant_barrel.\n- review::.::holistic::dependency_health::dual_http_clients: not-worth-it \u2014 requests is only in 2 files (browser_tool.py, model_metadata.py) in simple synchronous contexts; migration effort exceeds benefit.\n- review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::tools_init_redundant_barrel: not-worth-it \u2014 same reasoning as large_tools_init_barrel; registry handles dynamic loading already; barrel removal is a breaking change.\n- unused_enums::tests/tools/test_daytona_environment.py::_SandboxState: false positive \u2014 used at line 43 as `daytona_mod.SandboxState = _SandboxState`; detector misidentified mock assignment as unused enum.\n- unused_enums::tools/skills_tool.py::SkillReadinessStatus: false positive \u2014 used extensively at lines 401, 405, 887, 1122, 1124, 1139.\n",
